      p(style="font-size:20px; line-height: 150%;")
        | I studied Computer Science and Business through the Jerome Fisher Management and Technology dual-degree program at Penn. After that, I worked in Management Consulting with Bain and Company in New York, where I had the opportunity to tackle some meaty Fortune 500 company strategy problems in various fields. 
      p(style="font-size:20px; line-height: 150%;")
        | One project I've worked on at Facebook that I am incredibly passionate about is internet.org. About 80% of the world's population lives within range of a 2G or 3G connection, and yet well over 4B people remain unconnected to the internet. I've gotten to partner with carriers to find economically sustainable ways to make mobile data more affordable and accessible for the world. I love what a rich support network I have in my RPM class. We are all working on such different things, and yet many of the challenges we face are universal.
